 on the wind structures that made “Ash Wednesday” catastrophic.
 It highlighted that not only the mobility of the frontal system created
 this extreme fire event, but also the depth of the trough system.
 In this study, the cold front arrival was simulated with a 1-hour lag.
 Over time, computer simulations of extreme fire events in this region have
 become more sophisticated.
 
\end_layout

